M|references|source: wiki/concepts/Mental Models/Boy Scout Rule.md
M|references|created: 2026-04-11
M|references|rv-by: 2026-07-11
M|references|tailored-for: dec-critic
M|references|> "Always leave the codebase cleaner than you found it."
M|references|Attribution: Robert C. Martin (Uncle Bob)
M|references|Make small improvements continuously. Do not wait for dedicated refactoring sprints. Incremental improvement prevents rot. Compounding effect over time.
M|references|When evaluating decisions that involve code changes, assess scope boundaries:
M|references|| Claim Type | Critique Question |
M|references||------------|-------------------|
M|references|| "While fixing this, I should also..." | Is the additional work within the touched area? |
M|references|| "This needs refactoring first" | Can the fix proceed without the refactor? |
M|references|| "I'll clean this up while I'm here" | Will cleanup delay delivery? |
M|references|When validating improvement decisions:
M|references|| VERIFIED | FAILED | UNCERTAIN |
M|references||----------|--------|-----------|
M|references|| Change is in touched code area | Change unrelated to current work | Scope unclear from ctx |
M|references|| Small, safe improvement | Large refactoring bundled with fix | Risk assessment missing |
M|references|| Balanced with delivery | Perfectionism blocking progress | Trade-offs not articulated |
M|references|During dec critique, flag these patterns:
M|references|- "While I'm here" expanding to major work
M|references|- Scope creep in PRs
M|references|- Delivery blocked by improvement claims
M|references|- No clear connection between improvement and original goal
M|references|When reaching verdict on improvement decisions:
M|references|- **STAND**: Improvement clearly scoped to touched area, safe, and not blocking delivery
M|references|- **REVISE**: Scope unclear or trade-offs not addressed; needs boundary clarification
M|references|- **ESCALATE**: Large refactoring masquerading as small improvement; requires separate planning
M|references|- **Chesterton's Fence**: Understand before changing
M|references|- **Strangler Fig Pattern**: Incremental migration for larger changes